import React from 'react'
import Form from 'react-bootstrap/Form';
import Button from 'react-bootstrap/Button';


export const DosageDogs = () => {

  let name = " "; 
  let grams = 0;
  let ml = 0;

  return (
    <>
    
    <Form.Select aria-label="Default select example">
      <option>How much food you need based on your dogs weight ?</option>
      <option value="1">5kg = 100g</option>
      <option value="2">10kg = 200g</option>
      <option value="3">15kg = 300g</option>
      <option value="4">20kg = 400g</option>
    </Form.Select>

    <Form.Select aria-label="Default select example">
      <option>How much water you need based on your dogs weight ?</option>
      <option value="1">5kg = 250ml</option>
      <option value="2">10kg = 500ml</option>
      <option value="3">15kg = 750ml</option>
      <option value="4">20kg = 1000ml</option>
    </Form.Select>
      
    <Form>
      <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formBasicEmail">
        <Form.Label>Email address</Form.Label>
        <Form.Control type="email" placeholder="Enter email" />
        <Form.Text className="text-muted">
          We'll never share your email with anyone else.
        </Form.Text>
      </Form.Group>

      <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formBasicPassword">
        <Form.Label>Password</Form.Label>
        <Form.Control type="password" placeholder="Password" />
      </Form.Group>
      <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formBasicCheckbox">
        <Form.Check type="checkbox" label="Check me out" />
      </Form.Group>
      <Button variant="primary" type="submit">
        Submit
      </Button>
    </Form>

      </>
    
  );
}
